- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the deployment of road-side nodes for ITS applications, which involves network planning and infrastructure placement. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper considers strict QoS constraints, which are related to information theory. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper presents an agile strategy for deploying road-side nodes, which involves system design and control. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security and privacy concerns related to ITS applications. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also less likely but possible as the paper may use AI techniques for optimizing the deployment of road-side nodes.
